decision_conditions:
Condition 26 is amended as follows:

CONDITION: Prior to occupation of the development, to ensure compliance with the principles of Inclusive Design, the following amendments/details shall be provided unless otherwise agreed in writing:  

a) No consent is granted for the proposed revolving ground floor entrance door. Details of a revised design of the proposed entrance door which ensures compliance with section 4.4 of the Inclusive Design in Islington SPD, shall be provided and approved by the Local Planning Authority;  
b) Details regarding the provision of five accessible cycle racks within the development which will be installed prior to occupation of the development; c) Winding treads incorporated shall be limited to Core 1 (on half landings between 1st and 5th floors) and to fire escape Core 3 (between 1st and 3rd floors) only;  
d) Details of the outward opening door to each wheel chair accessible toilet;  
e) Provision shall be made for a disabled toilet for ambulant disabled people in addition to in the wheelchair accessible toilet.  

REASON: In order to facilitate and promote inclusive and sustainable communities.
